Let $X_1$ and $X_2$ be the spaces
\begin{align*}
X_1&=\{(x,y)\in \mathbb{R}^2 : (x,y)\neq(0,0)\}, \\
X_2&=\{(x,y)\in \mathbb{R}^2 : (x,y)\notin [0,1]\times\{0\}\}.
\end{align*}
Are these spaces homeomorphic? If these spaces are homeomorphic, what is the homeomorphism map? If these spaces are not homeomorphic, why? I suspect these spaces are homeomorphic, but I can't construct homeomorphism.
